{"title_page": "Unsepttrium", "text_new": "#REDIRECT [[Extended periodic table#Beyond element 172]]\n\nUnsepttrium is a hypothetical alkali metal with the atomic number of 173 and symbol of Ust. Unsepttrium has an atomic mass of 507. Unsepttrium might be radioactive because it is a superheavy element and many superheavy elements are radioactive. Unsepttrium might be essential to life. If so it will be the third alkali metal essential to the human body after sodium and potassium , two other alkali metals that already exist. Unsepttrium has an electron configuration of Usb 6g1. Unsepttrium can lose its only valence electron forming the Ust+ ion forming compounds with the halogens forming salts that might be essential to humans. Unsepttrium might be synthetic. If so it might be the second synthetic alkali metal after Ununennium another hypothetical alkali metal.\n", "text_old": "#REDIRECT [[Extended periodic table#Beyond element 172]]\n\n{{rcat shell|\n{{Wikidata redirect}}\n{{R with possibilities}}\n{{R from subtopic}}\n{{R printworthy}}\n}}\n\n[[Category:Hypothetical chemical elements]]\n", "name_user": "2606:a000:121c:44d:2118:8d00:5f9b:33ce", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(I edited the page because I wanted to make a new page on the Wikipedia.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Unsepttrium&redirect=no"}
{"title_page": "1987\u201388 Balkans Cup", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox football tournament season\n| title = Balkans Cup\n| year = 1987\u201388\n| country = [[Balkans]]\n| num_teams = 10\n| champions = {{Flagicon|BUL|1971}} '''[[PFC Slavia Sofia|Slavia Sofia]]'''\n| runner-up = {{Flagicon|ROM|1965}} [[FC Arge\u0219 Pite\u0219ti|Arge\u0219 Pite\u0219ti]]\n| matches = 30\n| goals = 110\n| prevseason = [[1986 Balkans Cup|1986]]\n| nextseason = [[1988\u201389 Balkans Cup|1988\u201389]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1987\u201388 Balkans Cup''' was an edition of the [[Balkans Cup]], a [[association football|football]] competition for representative clubs from the [[Balkans|Balkan]] states. It was contested by 10 teams and [[PFC Slavia Sofia|Slavia Sofia]] won the trophy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=rsssf.com|title=Balkans Cup 1987\u201388 season|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/balkanclub80s.html|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n==Group A==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style = WDL\n|section = Group A\n|source = [http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/balkanclub80s.html rsssf.com]\n<!--Team positions-->\n|team1 = ARG |team2 = SLS |team3 = LUF |team4 = PAO\n<!-- Team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1 = Q\n|result2 = RU\n<!--Team results here-->\n|update = complete\n|use_goal_ratio = yes\n|win_ARG = 4 |draw_ARG = 1 |loss_ARG = 1 |gf_ARG = 10 |ga_ARG = 5 <!-- ARG -->\n|win_SLS = 3 |draw_SLS = 0 |loss_SLS = 3 |gf_SLS = 9 |ga_SLS = 7 <!-- SLS -->\n|win_LUF = 2 |draw_LUF = 1 |loss_LUF = 3 |gf_LUF = 6 |ga_LUF = 12 <!-- LUF -->\n|win_PAO = 2 |draw_PAO = 0 |loss_PAO = 4 |gf_PAO = 10 |ga_PAO = 11 <!-- PAO -->\n<!--Team definitions (wikilinks in table)-->\n|name_ARG = {{Flagicon|ROM|1965}} [[FC Arge\u0219 Pite\u0219ti|Arge\u0219 Pite\u0219ti]]\n|name_SLS = {{Flagicon|BUL|1971}} [[PFC Slavia Sofia|Slavia Sofia]]\n|name_LUF = {{Flagicon|ALB}} [[Luft\u00ebtari Gjirokast\u00ebr]]\n|name_PAO = {{Flagicon|GRE|}} [[PAOK FC|PAOK]]\n\n<!--Table settings and rules-->\n|winpoin